## Title Construction Rules

### DO:
- Lead with your technology/method
- Use "for" to connect technology to application
- Include ONE key advantage (don't overload)
- Keep total length: 8-15 words optimal
- Be specific about the disease/target

### DON'T:
- Use "Novel" or "New" (assumed for publications)
- Include system acronyms in title (save for abstract)
- List multiple diseases unless truly multiplex
- Use vague terms like "improved" or "enhanced"
- Make the title a full sentence

